PROOF VIABILITY ASSESSMENT
==============================================================================

Cases with M(p) ≤ -3: 5
  All ΔW < 0: True
  All ratio > 1 (ET criterion): True

Can we prove it using ONLY the m=1 term?
  m=1 term of δΣ = -2·M(p-1) + 1
  For M(p) ≤ -3: M(p-1) ≤ -2, so m=1 term ≥ 5

  Need: n₁ · δΣ > (p-1) · Σ₁
  With δΣ ≥ m=1 term + (positive diagonal terms):
  We need to lower-bound δΣ and upper-bound Σ₁.

  m=1 fraction of δΣ for M(p)≤-3 cases:
    min: 18.7%
    max: 41.2%
    avg: 28.5%

THEORETICAL BOUND:
  δΣ ≥ (-2M(p-1)+1) + Σ_{m≥2} c_p(m)²/m²
      = (-2M(p-1)+1) + Σ_{p∤m,m≥2} 1/m² + Σ_{k≥1} (p-1)²/(pk)²
      ≥ (-2M(p-1)+1) + [π²/6 - 1 - Σ_{p|m} 1/m²] + (p-1)²/p² · π²/6
      ≥ (-2M(p-1)+1) + (π²/6 - 1 - π²/(6p²)) + (1-1/p)² · π²/6

  Σ_{m≥2} 1/m² = π²/6 - 1 ≈ 0.6449
  For p=5 (smallest with M(p)=-3):
    M(4) = -1, m=1 term = 3

